notes.title: Tenant Concessions 11/1/2024-10/31/2025
notes.body:
Nature of Concessions:
Quarterly Housekeeping Services:
a. Service Description: The Landlord agrees to provide quarterly housekeeping services at 541 W Addison St Apt 3S. These services shall be provided during February, May and August 2025.
b. Services Include:
i. General Cleaning: Dusting, vacuuming, and mopping of all floors.
ii. Kitchen Cleaning: Cleaning of countertops, sinks, exterior
surfaces of appliances, and cabinet fronts.
iii. Bathroom Cleaning: Cleaning of toilets, sinks, showers, tubs, and
iv. Living Areas and Bedrooms: Dusting and cleaning of surfaces,
vacuuming carpets, and mopping hard floors.
c. Value of Services: The value of these services is Two Hundred Fifty Dollars ($250) per session.
d. Scheduling and Access: The Landlord or service provider will contact the Tenant two weeks in advance to confirm each session. The Tenant must ensure access to the premises on scheduled dates. If absent, the Tenant must arrange access.
e. Tenant Responsibilities: The Tenant must maintain general tidiness between visits. Additional cleaning services outside the quarterly schedule are the Tenant's responsibility and may incur charges
f. Service Provider: The Landlord reserves the right to choose and change the service provider

2.
g. Non-Transferability and Cash Value: These services are non-transferable and have no cash value. They cannot be exchanged for money or other benefits.
h. Cancellation or Rescheduling: The Tenant must notify the Landlord 48 hours in advance to reschedule. The Landlord will attempt to accommodate rescheduling.
i. Termination of Lease: If the Tenant vacates or the lease is terminated, any remaining services are forfeited and will not be refunded or prorated.
Liability: The Landlord is not liable for any damages or losses from the housekeeping services, except for gross negligence or willful misconduct.
Lease Extension Incentive:
a. Description: If the Tenant signs an addendum to extend the lease to 18 months prior to the end of the year 2024, the following incentives will be provided:
i. Rent Discount: A discount of Three Hundred Dollars ($300) off the January 2025 rent.
ii. Fitness Membership: A three-month Single Club Access membership to FFC (Fitness Formula Clubs).
b. Value of Incentive: The total value of the fitness membership is $487, which includes $129 per month for three months and a $100
c. Eligibility: This incentive is only available if the lease extension addendum is signed before December 31, 2024.
d. Non-Transferability and Cash Value: These incentives are non-transferable and have no cash value. They cannot be exchanged for money or other benefits.
e. Confirmation: The Landlord will confirm the application of the rent discount and provide details on how to activate the fitness membership upon receipt of the signed lease extension addendum..

properties.name: City Studio at The Commodore
properties.description:
The iconic Commodore building is a historic property with a rich history dating back to the early 20th century.
Built in 1898, The Commodore is a Chicago landmark known for its elegant Beaux-Arts architecture, featuring a classic U-shaped courtyard design that fosters a sense of community and timeless charm.
Originally constructed as a luxury apartment hotel, The Commodore was later converted into condominiums and now houses over 100 unique units, blending historic character with modern updates.
Managed by the Commodore Greenbriar Landmark Condo Association, the building remains a cornerstone of the Lakeview East neighborhood, offering residents a well-maintained and secure living environment. Its prime location provides easy access to Lake Michigan, vibrant nightlife, & a variety of dining and shopping options.
City Studio by ARIBIA reflects its heritage, while offering contemporary amenities, creating a harmonious blend of history & modern living. 

www.CommodoreChicago.com

properties.name: Cozy Castle at The Commodore
properties.description:
Historic luxury meets modern convenience at The Commodore, 550 W Surf. Built in 1897 by architect Edmund R. Krause, this six‑story Roman‑brick landmark anchors Lakeview East’s Surf‑Pine Grove historic district. Beyond the gated courtyard await elevator service, bike storage, package room, new sprinklers, and on‑site management - also included is cable and gigabit internet. Inside, original woodwork, oversized windows, and a legendary 6th‑floor ballroom rumored to host Capone‑era soirées deliver Gilded‑Age drama. Trader Joe’s, Target, gyms, lakefront trail, and Wrigley Field are minutes away.

https://CommodoreChicago.com

properties.name: Lakeside Loft at Addison Lakeshore West
properties.description:
Addison Lakeshore West is a beautifully preserved vintage courtyard building in Chicago’s Lakeview neighborhood, constructed in the 1920s. This boutique-style property combines timeless architectural charm with modern-day convenience. Its standout feature is a landscaped courtyard, complete with manicured gardens, mature trees, & a tranquil fountain, offering a serene retreat from city life.

The building emphasizes secure living with an access control system, ensuring privacy & peace of mind for all residents. Pet-friendly, the property welcomes your furry companions, fostering a community-oriented environment. With only a limited number of units, residents enjoy an intimate, close-knit atmosphere that is ideal for those seeking a quieter urban lifestyle.

Situated just steps from Lake Michigan, public transportation & renowned dining & shopping, Lakeside Loft is a harmonious blend of history, style, & convenience, making it a true gem in the heart of Lakeview  LakesideLoftChicago.com
